<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911220-0127</DOCNO><DOCID>911220-0127.</DOCID><HL>   Nord Sells $20 Million of Debt</HL><DATE>12/20/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   A.CRT NRD</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED MINING (MNG)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>AUSTRALIA (ASA)FAR EAST (FE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   DAYTON, Ohio -- Nord Resources Corp. said it received $20million from Consolidated Rutile Ltd., an Australian rutilemining concern, in exchange for $20 million of 10-year, 8%convertible debentures.   Nord, which makes natural rutile -- a premium titaniumdioxide material -- as well as kaolin and perlite, said itwould use the proceeds to prepay certain bank debts and forworking capital.</LP><TEXT>   In connection with the sale, Nord said the two companieshave agreed that, subject to certain conditions, ConsolidatedRutile will increase its stake in Nord to more than 30%.</TEXT></DOC>